1
00:00:30,240 --> 00:00:35,760
♪ I was like a sun without rays of light ♪

2
00:00:35,760 --> 00:00:38,920
♪ I never mattered ♪

3
00:00:39,000 --> 00:00:43,840
♪ With no one to rely on ♪

4
00:00:43,840 --> 00:00:49,280
♪ Until you came along and changed everything in me ♪

5
00:00:49,280 --> 00:00:52,600
♪ Helped me find true love ♪

6
00:00:52,600 --> 00:00:56,520
♪ And realize who to live for ♪

7
00:00:57,280 --> 00:01:00,600
♪ Once looked lonely ♪

8
00:01:00,680 --> 00:01:03,280
♪ I'm now filled with your shadow ♪

9
00:01:03,280 --> 00:01:09,160
♪ As the light to my heart ♪

10
00:01:11,000 --> 00:01:15,080
♪ You are the moon in my heart ♪

11
00:01:15,080 --> 00:01:19,720
♪ You make everything ♪

12
00:01:19,720 --> 00:01:23,880
♪ More meaningful every day ♪

13
00:01:23,960 --> 00:01:29,360
♪ I wanna be your sun ♪

14
00:01:29,360 --> 00:01:33,200
♪ Please let me ♪

15
00:01:33,200 --> 00:01:39,880
♪ Be by your side
And keep on loving you ♪

16
00:01:44,880 --> 00:01:47,240
Thank you very much for saving me today.

17
00:01:47,240 --> 00:01:48,760
Her name is Tawan.

18
00:01:48,760 --> 00:01:49,680
She's in Grade 12.

19
00:01:49,680 --> 00:01:52,440
And she's our school's kendo champion.

20
00:01:55,880 --> 00:01:56,960
Tawan?

21
00:01:56,960 --> 00:01:58,920
Don't forget who you are.

22
00:01:59,000 --> 00:02:01,120
Follow your dreams.

23
00:02:01,120 --> 00:02:03,520
I'll always be rooting for you.

24
00:02:03,600 --> 00:02:05,400
Hasn't Tawan told you?

25
00:02:05,480 --> 00:02:07,720
She moved to another school.

26
00:02:07,720 --> 00:02:10,120
When I'm successful enough,

27
00:02:10,120 --> 00:02:14,840
you will see me then, and I will get you back.

28
00:02:17,720 --> 00:02:19,600
Hello, everyone. It's me, Ayla.

29
00:02:19,600 --> 00:02:23,600
Today, I'll unwrap the gifts from my fans.

30
00:02:24,200 --> 00:02:25,960
Let's start at the first box.

31
00:02:30,320 --> 00:02:32,160
Oh, my God.

32
00:02:32,680 --> 00:02:35,240
Guys, it's something I collect.

33
00:02:41,200 --> 00:02:42,400
Guys.

34
00:02:42,720 --> 00:02:44,760
This one comes with a rose.

35
00:02:46,520 --> 00:02:47,920
Let's see what's inside.

36
00:03:08,680 --> 00:03:13,120
Guys, I think I'm being pranked by the crew.

37
00:03:13,520 --> 00:03:15,400
Halloween is coming up.

38
00:03:16,160 --> 00:03:17,160
That's right.

39
00:03:21,000 --> 00:03:23,080
I don't want your apology.

40
00:03:23,600 --> 00:03:26,960
I want to know where Ayla's safety was.

41
00:03:27,040 --> 00:03:29,640
How could your crew let in someone like that?

42
00:03:29,960 --> 00:03:32,160
Don't you guys check these things first?

43
00:03:32,160 --> 00:03:33,960
We're looking into it

44
00:03:34,040 --> 00:03:37,320
to see how that box got mixed into Ayla's gifts.

45
00:03:37,800 --> 00:03:40,840
The crew member in charge of her gifts said
they'd never seen that box.

46
00:03:41,720 --> 00:03:43,040
You mean

47
00:03:43,120 --> 00:03:46,920
someone slipped into the studio that easily?

48
00:03:47,280 --> 00:03:51,600
Or anyone can just walk right into
your company at any time?

49
00:03:51,680 --> 00:03:53,800
Uh, that's not true.

50
00:03:53,800 --> 00:03:56,960
We have around-the-clock security guards.

51
00:03:57,360 --> 00:03:58,960
I don't think that's enough.

52
00:03:59,320 --> 00:04:01,800
This isn't the first time something happens to Ayla.

53
00:04:01,800 --> 00:04:07,040
Your president promised me
Ayla's safety always came first.

54
00:04:08,000 --> 00:04:11,080
That was why I let her sign with your record company.

55
00:04:11,680 --> 00:04:16,600
Mr. Thana, we're going to boost her security detail.

56
00:04:17,000 --> 00:04:18,200
I don't want it.

57
00:04:18,720 --> 00:04:20,680
I no longer trust your company.

58
00:04:21,279 --> 00:04:21,880
Dad.

59
00:04:25,520 --> 00:04:28,280
I'll find my daughter's bodyguard myself.

60
00:04:28,960 --> 00:04:29,800
Goodbye.

61
00:04:33,920 --> 00:04:34,920
Dad.

62
00:04:35,680 --> 00:04:37,240
No need to get angry.

63
00:04:37,240 --> 00:04:38,640
I'm not hurt.

64
00:04:39,000 --> 00:04:40,720
I'm just a little shaken up.

65
00:04:41,120 --> 00:04:43,200
It's not something to take lightly.

66
00:04:43,960 --> 00:04:47,080
You've been getting too many horrible things.

67
00:04:52,920 --> 00:04:56,520
Give me a list of security companies and their profiles.

68
00:04:57,640 --> 00:04:59,960
I'm looking for my daughter's bodyguard.

69
00:05:06,600 --> 00:05:07,600
Dad,

70
00:05:07,880 --> 00:05:11,400
about the security companies, I know of one.

71
00:05:11,480 --> 00:05:13,680
Their profile looks great too.

72
00:05:13,760 --> 00:05:19,280
They take care of international artists
and nation leaders who visit Thailand.

73
00:05:19,800 --> 00:05:21,000
Sounds good, right?

74
00:05:21,640 --> 00:05:22,920
Are you interested?

75
00:05:35,000 --> 00:05:36,200
Go!

76
00:05:41,320 --> 00:05:42,320
Clear!

77
00:05:49,800 --> 00:05:50,800
Clear!

78
00:05:59,880 --> 00:06:00,880
Get down!

79
00:06:17,240 --> 00:06:18,240
Go.

80
00:06:28,680 --> 00:06:29,760
Mission complete!

81
00:06:46,760 --> 00:06:48,200
But three minutes late.

82
00:06:50,480 --> 00:06:51,640
Gee, boss.

83
00:06:54,160 --> 00:06:55,360
Well...

84
00:06:55,360 --> 00:06:58,000
Tim was too tough today. I wasted a lot of bullets.

85
00:06:59,520 --> 00:07:02,120
So, you lost your touch and missed your target?

86
00:07:02,560 --> 00:07:05,760
I didn't miss, sis, but it just a graze.

87
00:07:06,800 --> 00:07:08,840
At least you completed your mission.

88
00:07:09,840 --> 00:07:12,680
Anyone know what mistake
cost you those three minutes?

89
00:07:13,400 --> 00:07:16,760
Ya and I got all our targets, boss.

90
00:07:20,400 --> 00:07:22,120
But the hostage hurt her leg.

91
00:07:25,160 --> 00:07:27,320
What happened to your leg?

92
00:07:27,920 --> 00:07:30,760
I sprained it while rushing down.

93
00:07:31,560 --> 00:07:36,680
I see. That's why I felt
she slowed down after that point.

94
00:07:37,440 --> 00:07:38,640
I'm sorry.

95
00:07:40,880 --> 00:07:42,160
We'll get you some ice.

96
00:07:43,640 --> 00:07:45,640
Nana, take care of her.

97
00:07:46,200 --> 00:07:47,320
Yes, boss.

98
00:07:47,560 --> 00:07:48,560
Please come.

99
00:07:52,360 --> 00:07:54,400
Boss, so what did I do wrong

100
00:07:54,640 --> 00:07:56,200
that allowed Tim to respond?

101
00:07:56,280 --> 00:07:59,120
Instead of taking away his gun as fast as possible,

102
00:07:59,120 --> 00:08:02,440
you got cocky and gave him time to respond.

103
00:08:03,840 --> 00:08:04,840
Time?

104
00:08:05,360 --> 00:08:06,320
When?

105
00:08:08,800 --> 00:08:09,720
Tim.

106
00:08:24,440 --> 00:08:27,400
Boss, a potential client just contacted us via email.

107
00:08:28,600 --> 00:08:30,120
Chanya, help Nana.

108
00:08:30,640 --> 00:08:31,640
Yes, boss.

109
00:08:35,520 --> 00:08:36,919
"Class C"

110
00:08:37,919 --> 00:08:40,360
(Personal information)

111
00:08:43,240 --> 00:08:44,640
Not right for me.

112
00:08:46,760 --> 00:08:48,120
Not right for her.

113
00:08:50,760 --> 00:08:52,200
(Personal information)

114
00:09:18,160 --> 00:09:19,600
None of them either.

115
00:09:19,880 --> 00:09:20,680
Are there more?

116
00:09:22,800 --> 00:09:23,800
Yes.

117
00:09:25,960 --> 00:09:27,720
"Are there more?"

118
00:09:27,720 --> 00:09:29,320
-Huh?
-Yeah.

119
00:09:29,600 --> 00:09:31,560
The next set is Class A.

120
00:09:34,680 --> 00:09:36,120
This is a sure thing.

121
00:09:36,120 --> 00:09:40,680
(Personal information)

122
00:09:44,120 --> 00:09:45,480
Still no for me.

123
00:09:47,800 --> 00:09:48,840
Huh?

124
00:09:50,840 --> 00:09:51,840
Give me that.

125
00:09:55,680 --> 00:09:57,160
Don't tell me.

126
00:09:57,160 --> 00:09:59,080
Mm, she didn't pick anyone.

127
00:09:59,560 --> 00:10:00,840
Now what, Ya?

128
00:10:07,160 --> 00:10:09,680
No one meets the VIP's criteria?

129
00:10:10,160 --> 00:10:11,400
Not even Class A?

130
00:10:12,280 --> 00:10:13,400
Yes, boss.

131
00:10:13,720 --> 00:10:15,760
That's why Ya's pissed off, boss.

132
00:10:18,960 --> 00:10:20,040
Nana.

133
00:10:21,000 --> 00:10:23,040
Make an appointment with the VIP.

134
00:10:23,280 --> 00:10:24,560
I'll talk to them myself.

135
00:10:25,480 --> 00:10:26,600
Yes, boss.

136
00:10:32,000 --> 00:10:34,600
(Contract Termination Letter)

137
00:10:38,320 --> 00:10:42,960
Ms. Rawee, does your company
really have no one else for us?

138
00:10:43,640 --> 00:10:45,200
As far as I know,

139
00:10:45,880 --> 00:10:48,680
from Class C to Class A,

140
00:10:49,120 --> 00:10:52,120
no one meets the VIP's criteria at all.

141
00:10:53,600 --> 00:10:58,520
As a result, it's our responsibility
to terminate this contract.

142
00:11:01,160 --> 00:11:04,240
I don't think we need to
look for another company, Dad.

143
00:11:43,520 --> 00:11:45,800
If we don't find another company,

144
00:11:46,040 --> 00:11:48,240
how will you find your bodyguard?

145
00:11:48,240 --> 00:11:49,640
You didn't choose anyone.

146
00:11:50,200 --> 00:11:51,920
I already chose someone.

147
00:11:59,040 --> 00:12:02,040
Will you be my bodyguard, Ms. Rawee?

148
00:12:05,720 --> 00:12:09,280
Or you're not brave enough to take care of me?

149
00:12:29,480 --> 00:12:31,760
If that's what you wish,

150
00:12:33,080 --> 00:12:35,600
our company's happy to oblige.

151
00:12:38,520 --> 00:12:42,720
I'm happy too that
I'm getting an S-class to take care of me.

152
00:12:46,640 --> 00:12:48,560
Can you start tomorrow?

153
00:12:52,240 --> 00:12:56,360
But why don't we find you a few more bodyguards?

154
00:12:56,680 --> 00:12:59,160
I think one is too few.

155
00:13:04,360 --> 00:13:06,240
I need only one.

156
00:13:10,840 --> 00:13:14,400
Looking forward to working with you, Ms. Bodyguard.

157
00:13:19,480 --> 00:13:24,120
♪ You are the moon in my heart ♪

158
00:13:24,120 --> 00:13:28,800
♪ You make everything ♪

159
00:13:28,800 --> 00:13:33,080
♪ More meaningful every day ♪

160
00:13:33,080 --> 00:13:38,440
♪ I wanna be your sun ♪

161
00:13:38,440 --> 00:13:42,280
♪ Please let me ♪

162
00:13:42,280 --> 00:13:48,520
♪ Be by your side and keep on loving you ♪

163
00:13:54,760 --> 00:13:55,560
Let's go.

164
00:13:56,440 --> 00:13:58,440
See? Here comes my boss.

165
00:13:58,440 --> 00:14:00,920
I told you she'd clear things up in no time.

166
00:14:02,760 --> 00:14:04,360
We're not in trouble, right, boss?

167
00:14:04,880 --> 00:14:08,200
They just let us terminate the contract
and we're not liable, right?

168
00:14:08,520 --> 00:14:09,640
We'll talk at the office.

169
00:14:11,600 --> 00:14:12,560
But, boss,

170
00:14:12,640 --> 00:14:15,040
the termination letter hasn't been signed.

171
00:14:15,320 --> 00:14:16,480
Eh?

172
00:14:16,480 --> 00:14:17,200
Yeah.

173
00:14:19,480 --> 00:14:21,360
Why... Oh?

174
00:14:27,640 --> 00:14:30,520
See you tomorrow, Tawan.

175
00:14:35,760 --> 00:14:37,160
No termination.

176
00:14:37,160 --> 00:14:38,440
"See you tomorrow."

177
00:14:39,080 --> 00:14:40,280
So you accepted the job?

178
00:14:42,120 --> 00:14:43,040
Boss...

179
00:14:43,040 --> 00:14:44,840
-Boss, what does this mean?
-Boss, what...

180
00:14:44,840 --> 00:14:45,920
Quiet.

181
00:14:46,680 --> 00:14:48,320
We'll talk at the office.

182
00:14:56,840 --> 00:15:00,480
She's a famous idol.
Don't you know about her? Do you watch TV?

183
00:15:04,000 --> 00:15:05,320
She's waving. Where are you going?

184
00:15:06,840 --> 00:15:08,760
-You go first.
-Boss's still here.

185
00:15:09,720 --> 00:15:10,720
Go.

186
00:15:11,040 --> 00:15:12,200
We're leaving?

187
00:15:12,920 --> 00:15:14,600
Hey, why didn't you close the gate?

188
00:15:28,480 --> 00:15:31,400
(Related Parties: Thana - father,
Khaotu - friend, Kaew - maid, Ji - driver)

189
00:15:47,120 --> 00:15:48,520
Don't you have anything to do?

190
00:15:49,200 --> 00:15:50,480
-No.
-No.

191
00:16:02,160 --> 00:16:04,160
Please brief us on the mission.

192
00:16:12,320 --> 00:16:14,000
You saw the VIP.

193
00:16:14,440 --> 00:16:16,080
That's it. Nothing to it.

194
00:16:16,280 --> 00:16:19,200
But you usually don't accept jobs with artists.

195
00:16:21,560 --> 00:16:25,360
Well, I was the only one left and the VIP picked me.
You expect me to decline?

196
00:16:25,440 --> 00:16:27,560
Did she know you from before?

197
00:16:27,560 --> 00:16:29,960
I heard she call you, "Tawan."

198
00:16:31,520 --> 00:16:33,960
That's right. If I knew you two were close,

199
00:16:34,040 --> 00:16:37,120
I would've had you talk to her from the beginning.

200
00:16:38,640 --> 00:16:40,800
We met a long time ago.

201
00:16:41,080 --> 00:16:42,320
We're not close.

202
00:16:43,120 --> 00:16:45,520
Seems to me she wants to get close to you.

203
00:16:46,040 --> 00:16:47,720
She gave you a sweet smile.

204
00:16:47,720 --> 00:16:48,520
Like that.

205
00:16:53,960 --> 00:16:56,200
Boss actually did it for our company.

206
00:16:56,520 --> 00:16:57,560
Right, Nana?

207
00:16:58,200 --> 00:16:59,200
Yes.

208
00:16:59,760 --> 00:17:02,960
Boss, Ms. Ayla's actually gorgeous.

209
00:17:03,520 --> 00:17:05,000
Do you think

210
00:17:05,000 --> 00:17:08,040
you can ask her to give me her autograph?

211
00:17:10,240 --> 00:17:11,640
I see.

212
00:17:12,680 --> 00:17:13,960
I guess not.

213
00:17:14,839 --> 00:17:17,800
But honestly, Ms. Ayla's very beautiful.

214
00:17:18,119 --> 00:17:21,520
Beautiful, sexy, sings and dances amazingly.

215
00:17:21,599 --> 00:17:24,720
With that level of fame,
it's no surprise she has a stalker.

216
00:17:24,720 --> 00:17:25,520
True.

217
00:17:25,599 --> 00:17:30,200
Boss, I sent you all of Ms. Ayla's songs.

218
00:17:30,520 --> 00:17:31,920
So that you speak her language.

219
00:17:32,000 --> 00:17:33,640
What's going on here?

220
00:17:34,000 --> 00:17:36,240
Why do we need to listen to her songs?

221
00:17:36,240 --> 00:17:38,600
We're her bodyguards, not fans.

222
00:17:38,600 --> 00:17:39,800
-That's right.
-Well...

223
00:17:40,160 --> 00:17:41,840
The songs are a good idea.

224
00:17:44,200 --> 00:17:45,400
They're information.

225
00:17:46,000 --> 00:17:47,000
Huh?

226
00:18:07,720 --> 00:18:09,280
Ms. Rain Chaser.

227
00:18:12,280 --> 00:18:14,720
Is Tawan still as kind?

228
00:18:17,040 --> 00:18:18,440
Is she dating anyone?

229
00:18:21,760 --> 00:18:24,440
But there's no ring on both her ring fingers.

230
00:18:24,440 --> 00:18:26,160
She could still be single.

231
00:18:27,800 --> 00:18:28,800
Right?

232
00:18:31,200 --> 00:18:34,480
♪ Helped me find true love ♪

233
00:18:34,480 --> 00:18:39,160
♪ And realize who to live for ♪

234
00:18:39,160 --> 00:18:42,280
♪ Once looked lonely ♪

235
00:18:42,360 --> 00:18:45,160
♪ I'm now filled with your shadow ♪

236
00:18:45,160 --> 00:18:52,200
♪ As the light to my heart ♪

237
00:18:52,200 --> 00:18:57,120
♪ You are the moon in my heart ♪

238
00:18:57,120 --> 00:19:00,560
Will you be my bodyguard, Ms. Rawee?

239
00:19:01,520 --> 00:19:05,840
♪ More meaningful every day ♪

240
00:19:05,840 --> 00:19:11,280
♪ I wanna be your sun ♪

241
00:19:11,280 --> 00:19:15,080
♪ Please let me ♪

242
00:19:15,080 --> 00:19:21,640
♪ Be by your side and keep on loving you ♪

243
00:19:42,000 --> 00:19:43,600
Morning, Tawan.

244
00:19:44,880 --> 00:19:46,760
Hello, Ms. Ayla.

245
00:19:49,280 --> 00:19:51,960
May I request something from you?

246
00:19:52,880 --> 00:19:54,160
Go ahead, please.

247
00:19:55,160 --> 00:19:58,040
If I can provide it, then there's no problem.

248
00:20:00,360 --> 00:20:03,320
Do you mind speaking to me in

249
00:20:03,760 --> 00:20:05,520
a more casual way?

250
00:20:05,520 --> 00:20:07,440
This is way too formal.

251
00:20:07,800 --> 00:20:09,400
Oh, one more thing.

252
00:20:09,400 --> 00:20:15,040
I don't want people to gossip that
I take personal bodyguards everywhere.

253
00:20:15,440 --> 00:20:16,720
So...

254
00:20:23,040 --> 00:20:25,680
You want me in casual clothes.

255
00:20:31,800 --> 00:20:32,920
Sure.

256
00:21:14,920 --> 00:21:16,240
Wow.

257
00:21:17,520 --> 00:21:20,400
So professional. You really are an S-class.

258
00:21:21,320 --> 00:21:23,200
We have additional rules

259
00:21:23,880 --> 00:21:26,200
to inform you as well, Ms. Ayla.

260
00:21:54,120 --> 00:21:55,080
The last one.

261
00:21:56,080 --> 00:21:58,160
Always stay in the bodyguard's

262
00:21:58,880 --> 00:22:00,400
line of sight.

263
00:22:01,800 --> 00:22:03,400
"Line of sight"?

264
00:22:05,480 --> 00:22:07,320
How far is the line of sight?

265
00:22:10,960 --> 00:22:12,160
This far?

266
00:22:17,440 --> 00:22:18,840
Or this far?

267
00:22:35,680 --> 00:22:39,640
♪ I was like a sun without rays of light ♪

268
00:22:39,640 --> 00:22:40,720
Or this far?

269
00:22:41,200 --> 00:22:44,480
♪ I never mattered ♪

270
00:22:44,480 --> 00:22:49,000
♪ With no one to rely on ♪

271
00:22:49,000 --> 00:22:51,360
Am I in your sight now?

272
00:22:51,360 --> 00:22:54,760
♪ Until you came along and changed everything in me ♪

273
00:22:54,760 --> 00:22:58,080
♪ Helped me find true love ♪
